{
  "stem": "15686.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they would say empty your pockets.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they would take anything that they fancied, whether it was some change that we had to buy a snack or whether it was a pocket knife or some toy or whatever they felt like.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They usually didn't bother the books, because they weren't interested in books that much.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we never lost our school books and things.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But they would just take things and then after they had taken everything, they would make threats and say, well, don't come along here anymore.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The street is not for Jews.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they would kick us in the behind a little bit, and some of them would give us a punch in the nose sometimes.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It all depended on the mood they were in or if they had a bad day or a good day.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And sometimes one of them would say, oh, let him go.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They're just little kids and others would say no, you know, they're Jews, doesn't matter.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And yeah, it-- it became dangerous after a while in those terms.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we would take different ways to school, try to use different streets and different ways to get to and from school.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But there were just so many that you could take.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Never.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Never.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Never, because we were always outnumbered.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They never-- there was never a one-on-one situation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If there was a one-on-one situation-- let's say you met a kid that lived upstairs in the same apartment building, and he was wearing his Hitler Youth uniform, and he was going to a meeting, and we met on the staircase.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We'd say hi, hello, you know, or something like that, and-- but they would never bother you on a one-on-one basis.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
